SPECIFICATIONS:\
The specifications for both Summit and Sierra are as follows:\
1. IBM POWER processors and NVIDIA Volta GPUs\
2. Mellanox InfiniBand InterConnection Network\
3. IBM Elastic Storage\
4. Maximum Projected power envelope of 10 MW\
\
NVLINK: \

\f1 \cf5 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 The GPUs in Titan are connected today to the CPUs through a PCI Express (PCIe) interface, which limits how fast the GPU\'92s can access the CPU memory system. Summit will have a new high-bandwidth interconnect from NVIDIA, called NVLINK, and it will improve accelerated software application performance. With NVLink, the data moves between the CPU memory and GPU memory 5-12 times faster than PCIe, making GPU-accelerated applications run much faster on Summit.\
\
Unified Memory Feature:\
The faster data movement that comes with the NVLink, coupled with another feature known as Unified Memory, will simplify GPU accelerator programming. Unified Memory allows the programmer to treat the CPU and GPU memories as one block of memory. The programmer can operate on the data without worrying about whether it resides in the CPU\'92s or GPU\'92s memory.\
